title: National Youth Orchestra of Slovakia
text:
The National Youth Orchestra of Slovakia (SMO, Slovak: Slovenský mládežnícky orchester) was founded in 2016 in Bratislava, and it consists of 80 musicians aged 16 to 28.
The orchestra is a member of the European Federation of National Youth Orchestras. It performed at Young Euro Classic 2019.
